WEBVTT

1
00:00:38.205 --> 00:00:39.833
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

2
00:00:40.007 --> 00:00:42.238
Mrs. Landry. you're
looking lovely as ever.

3
00:00:42.442 --> 00:00:45.241
Jimmy McGill.

4
00:00:45.412 --> 00:00:46.539
What are you doing here?

5
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:48.614
I was in the area.
and I thought:

6
00:00:48.815 --> 00:00:51.250
"I wonder how my favorite
former client is doing."

7
00:00:51.418 --> 00:00:52.852
And I have cookies.

8
00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:55.750
Oh. you're so sweet. Come on in.

9
00:00:55.923 --> 00:00:58.324
After I made these.
I looked down...

10
00:00:58.525 --> 00:01:02.792
and I thought "Wow. that
looks just like your Felix."

11
00:01:02.963 --> 00:01:05.057
They do.

12
00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:08.464
- You're so thoughtful.
- Well. I was afraid you wouldn't be here.

13
00:01:08.635 --> 00:01:12.538
Thought with that settlement money.
you might've moved somewhere swankier.

14
00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:14.139
What do you mean?

15
00:01:14.341 --> 00:01:15.934
The settlement.

16
00:01:16.109 --> 00:01:17.441
The Sandpiper case?

17
00:01:17.611 --> 00:01:19.773
- That's gotta be wrapped up by now.
- Oh. that.

18
00:01:19.947 --> 00:01:23.247
That... That... That's
still years away.

19
00:01:23.417 --> 00:01:26.251
- You haven't settled?
- No. I don't know all the details yet...

20
00:01:26.453 --> 00:01:30.914
but Erin... Uh. Erin Brill of
Davis & Main. do you know her?

21
00:01:31.091 --> 00:01:35.620
Lovely girl. She reminds
me of a young Mary Martin.

22
00:01:35.796 --> 00:01:40.962
Oh. yes. I... I have met her. Just
a... She's a wonderful young lady.

23
00:01:41.134 --> 00:01:42.796
Well. she takes
care of all that...

24
00:01:43.003 --> 00:01:45.666
and she said there's
still a long way to go.

25
00:01:45.906 --> 00:01:48.273
But you've received
an offer. right?

26
00:01:48.442 --> 00:01:51.469
Something sent
to you in writing.

27
00:01:51.645 --> 00:01:54.137
I mean. something more
than just Erin and you chatting?

28
00:01:54.381 --> 00:01:55.508
Oh.

29
00:01:59.186 --> 00:02:01.985
It's probably all
here in this box.

30
00:02:02.155 --> 00:02:07.150
I can't make heads or tails of
it. but you are welcome to look.

31
00:02:07.327 --> 00:02:08.454
You sure?

32
00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:11.599
Of course. It's you.

33
00:02:12.766 --> 00:02:15.395
Well. uh. I gotta say...

34
00:02:16.336 --> 00:02:21.036
I can't blame you for getting
mixed up with all this. Heh.

35
00:02:21.341 --> 00:02:25.972
I mean. these legal notices. I mean.
no one really understands them.

36
00:02:26.179 --> 00:02:28.705
You know. I've got a law degree.

37
00:02:28.915 --> 00:02:31.180
Sometimes. I can't even. uh...

38
00:02:35.055 --> 00:02:37.149
I can't even. uh...

39
00:02:38.058 --> 00:02:39.058
[EXHALES AUDIBLY]

40
00:02:42.863 --> 00:02:44.729
You haven't. uh...

41
00:02:45.365 --> 00:02:46.856
accepted this?

42
00:02:47.067 --> 00:02:49.832
Erin says we should wait.

43
00:02:50.337 --> 00:02:51.805
But...

44
00:02:53.473 --> 00:02:55.908
Erin doesn't really
matter. does she?

45
00:02:56.076 --> 00:02:59.205
I mean. you're the
class representative.

46
00:02:59.479 --> 00:03:00.742
That's a big deal.

47
00:03:00.947 --> 00:03:04.577
That means you. and
you alone. decide. You're...

48
00:03:04.751 --> 00:03:08.847
You are the legal stand-in
for your friends and neighbors.

49
00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:13.687
I don't know about all that. Jimmy. I
just leave it all to the professionals.

50
00:03:14.561 --> 00:03:18.157
Yeah. Sure. sure.
Lawyers know best.

51
00:03:18.865 --> 00:03:20.356
But I'm sorry...

52
00:03:20.534 --> 00:03:23.561
if you won the lottery. I mean.
you'd take the lump sum. right?

53
00:03:23.737 --> 00:03:26.400
I mean. money now is
better than money later.

54
00:03:27.040 --> 00:03:29.373
- Bird in the hand?
- I suppose.

55
00:03:29.576 --> 00:03:32.045
More time to enjoy it.

56
00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:34.912
You really should talk to Erin.

57
00:03:35.082 --> 00:03:37.881
She knows all the ins and outs.

58
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:41.579
Ins and outs. Yeah. Erin
sure knows those. Heh.

59
00:03:42.089 --> 00:03:45.355
I'd be happy to
talk to Erin. Uh...

60
00:03:45.759 --> 00:03:50.094
But I just can't help but wonder
if she's taking every aspect into...

61
00:03:50.263 --> 00:03:52.023
[KNOCK ON DOOR THEN
WOMEN CHATTERING OUTSIDE]

62
00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:53.465
Oh. Jimmy.

63
00:03:53.633 --> 00:03:57.695
I completely forgot. I'm
on my way to chair yoga.

64
00:03:57.871 --> 00:03:59.703
I'm so sorry.

65
00:03:59.873 --> 00:04:01.603
Oh. it's okay. Um...

66
00:04:01.775 --> 00:04:06.236
I probably should be
going. I have a lot to do.

67
00:04:11.017 --> 00:04:12.246
Jimmy.

68
00:04:12.452 --> 00:04:15.286
- Jimmy.
- Rose. Myrtle. Helen.

69
00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:17.720
That chair yoga
really works. huh?

70
00:04:17.891 --> 00:04:19.325
You all look 10 years younger.

71
00:04:19.559 --> 00:04:22.927
- Oh. you honeydripper.
- Hey. hurry up. It starts in five minutes.

72
00:04:23.096 --> 00:04:26.066
- You wanna come with us?
- You're welcome to. We can have guests.

73
00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:29.725
I would love to. uh.
but I'm not dressed for it.

74
00:04:29.903 --> 00:04:32.099
So I'll take a rain check.

75
00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:34.741
Certainly. Thanks for
the cookies. Jimmy.

76
00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:36.466
Bye.

77
00:04:41.581 --> 00:04:43.140
That can't be right.

78
00:04:43.316 --> 00:04:45.444
Can't be right.

79
00:04:48.989 --> 00:04:52.551
Seventeen point four total.

80
00:04:52.793 --> 00:04:54.625
Thirty-three percent
is the common fund.

81
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:57.765
So I'm one-fifteenth.

82
00:04:57.931 --> 00:04:59.559
Fifteen into 17...

83
00:05:01.701 --> 00:05:03.670
Carry the two...

84
00:05:04.171 --> 00:05:07.505
One million. one
hundred and sixty.

85
00:05:08.441 --> 00:05:13.846
One million. one hundred
and sixty thousand.

86
00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:16.783
Heh. Holy shit.

87
00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:19.782
[♪♪♪]

88
00:05:36.803 --> 00:05:38.795
[CHATTERING]

89
00:05:52.886 --> 00:05:54.218
- Mr. Ehrmantraut?
- Yes.

90
00:05:54.421 --> 00:05:57.323
Sorry to keep you waiting.
It'll be right this way.

91
00:05:58.124 --> 00:06:00.650
Can I get you anything to
drink? Tea. water. espresso?

92
00:06:00.827 --> 00:06:03.524
No. I'm fine. Thank you.

93
00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:08.233
[CHATTERING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGES]

94
00:06:17.177 --> 00:06:18.645
[KNOCKS]

95
00:06:19.546 --> 00:06:22.106
- Ms. Rodarte-Quayle. I have your next...
- Yes. thank you.

96
00:06:22.282 --> 00:06:24.547
Mr. Ehrmantraut.
Lydia Rodarte-Quayle.

97
00:06:24.718 --> 00:06:25.718
Mike.

98
00:06:25.886 --> 00:06:27.354
Thanks. Justin.

99
00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:30.080
Have a seat. Um...

100
00:06:30.257 --> 00:06:31.691
Mike...

101
00:06:31.858 --> 00:06:36.853
HR sent up your start paperwork.
I-9. W-2. pretty standard.

102
00:06:38.698 --> 00:06:41.793
Could I have your driver's
license and Social Security card?

103
00:06:42.269 --> 00:06:45.706
- Why?
- My assistant needs to make a copy.

104
00:06:46.373 --> 00:06:50.105
How does this hire work.
exactly? Walk me through it.

105
00:06:50.277 --> 00:06:54.305
You'll receive a paycheck from Madrigal
in the amount of $10.000 per week.

106
00:06:54.481 --> 00:06:58.646
I believe at that rate. your employment
should be paid out in about 20 weeks.

107
00:06:58.818 --> 00:07:02.380
Mr. Fring has arranged to
cover FICA. Social Security...

108
00:07:02.555 --> 00:07:04.456
the entirety of the tax burden.

109
00:07:04.624 --> 00:07:06.456
I assume that's
all right with you?

110
00:07:09.329 --> 00:07:13.425
Good. So to that end. I have you
down as a "logistics consultant."

111
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:14.693
What is that?

112
00:07:15.135 --> 00:07:18.469
It's a person who
consults on logistics.

113
00:07:18.638 --> 00:07:20.470
Does it matter?

114
00:07:21.107 --> 00:07:23.838
I'm not long on logistics.

115
00:07:24.010 --> 00:07:27.777
"Security consultant" would
be better. I used to be a cop.

116
00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:32.480
That'll look better on work history than
your current employer. SMQ Parking.

117
00:07:32.652 --> 00:07:33.779
So...

118
00:07:33.954 --> 00:07:35.786
you take my money...

119
00:07:35.956 --> 00:07:38.357
run it through this joint.
and it's clean? That it?

120
00:07:38.525 --> 00:07:40.084
Yes.

121
00:07:40.527 --> 00:07:42.086
Who knows this operation?

122
00:07:42.262 --> 00:07:44.288
You? Anyone else?

123
00:07:44.464 --> 00:07:47.024
- No.
- You sure?

124
00:07:47.767 --> 00:07:51.431
May I ask what. precisely.
is your concern here?

125
00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:56.804
I'm concerned about what happens
if you put my real name in your books.

126
00:07:57.043 --> 00:07:59.638
Your Madrigal is a
German company.

127
00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:02.612
One thing I know about
Germans is they love a good audit.

128
00:08:05.151 --> 00:08:08.485
I oversee eight freight terminals
across Texas and the Southwest.

129
00:08:08.655 --> 00:08:13.992
Operating costs range between
$800.000 and $1 million per week.

130
00:08:14.361 --> 00:08:17.729
All due respect.
Mike. but your money?

131
00:08:17.897 --> 00:08:19.456
It's a rounding error.

132
00:08:19.632 --> 00:08:21.794
If the IRS or
anyone else looks...

133
00:08:21.968 --> 00:08:24.146
you're a contractor for a
multinational corporation...

134
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:27.299
with 114.000
employees worldwide.

135
00:08:27.474 --> 00:08:29.705
You're like every other
person in this building.

136
00:08:30.076 --> 00:08:32.170
Like you?

137
00:08:32.979 --> 00:08:35.141
You think I'm not on the books?

138
00:08:35.315 --> 00:08:36.578
I am.

139
00:08:36.783 --> 00:08:37.910
Under my own name.

140
00:08:38.084 --> 00:08:40.918
- This is the way you handled it before?
- Handled what?

141
00:08:41.087 --> 00:08:44.023
The money for
Fring's other guys.

142
00:08:44.991 --> 00:08:46.926
Other guys?

143
00:08:47.560 --> 00:08:49.927
This is the first
time I've done this...

144
00:08:50.096 --> 00:08:51.894
for anyone.

145
00:08:52.899 --> 00:08:54.993
I don't know what you do. but...

146
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:58.304
Mr. Fring must think
you're quite good at it.

147
00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:15.588
Twenty weeks.

148
00:09:15.822 --> 00:09:17.757
The sooner you're off
my books. the better.

149
00:09:17.924 --> 00:09:19.859
Justin?

150
00:09:26.966 --> 00:09:30.061
Can you make a copy of
these. please? Thank you.

151
00:09:33.339 --> 00:09:36.332
MIKE: Hmm.
- What?

152
00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:41.040
This is a very nice office.

153
00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:43.079
Thank you.

154
00:09:45.885 --> 00:09:48.445
Seem to be risking a
lot for a drug dealer.

155
00:09:49.355 --> 00:09:51.153
Drug dealer?

156
00:09:53.660 --> 00:09:54.787
[SCOFFS]

157
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:57.724
If that's all you think he is...

158
00:09:58.565 --> 00:10:00.500
then you don't
know Gustavo Fring.

159
00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:12.444
[SIGHS]

160
00:10:20.386 --> 00:10:22.252
Let me understand you.

161
00:10:22.422 --> 00:10:28.191
You're proposing to double our premiums
on every one of our practicing attorneys?

162
00:10:28.528 --> 00:10:32.192
We know this is abrupt.
New issues have come to light.

163
00:10:32.398 --> 00:10:34.333
New issues?

164
00:10:34.501 --> 00:10:36.470
You mean Mr. McGill's
testimony at the bar?

165
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:37.934
That's a part of it. Yes.

166
00:10:38.138 --> 00:10:42.269
After 25 years of paying full premiums.
I can count on one hand our claims.

167
00:10:42.442 --> 00:10:45.901
This is an underwriting decision.
You shouldn't take it personally.

168
00:10:46.112 --> 00:10:49.344
In some special circumstances. we
have been known to extend a rider.

169
00:10:49.516 --> 00:10:50.711
What kind of rider?

170
00:10:50.917 --> 00:10:54.684
A senior. management-level partner
who would supervise Charles' work.

171
00:10:54.854 --> 00:10:56.982
Attend court and client
meetings with him...

172
00:10:57.423 --> 00:10:58.652
review filings.

173
00:10:58.825 --> 00:11:02.455
We've done this for clients with a
high probability of health failure...

174
00:11:02.629 --> 00:11:04.749
- as a precaution. HOWARD:
What you're saying is...

175
00:11:04.864 --> 00:11:08.164
for any case Charles takes on.
another partner is tied up as well.

176
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:09.859
And we don't bill a penny more?

177
00:11:10.036 --> 00:11:11.504
This is ludicrous.

178
00:11:11.704 --> 00:11:14.139
The insurance industry
is heavily regulated.

179
00:11:14.307 --> 00:11:16.833
I can think of a dozen infractions
here off the top of my head.

180
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:18.205
Mr. McGill.

181
00:11:18.444 --> 00:11:20.811
You're hoping we'll
either find another carrier...

182
00:11:20.980 --> 00:11:23.540
or cut you an enormous
check. Win-win for you.

183
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:26.049
I assure you. neither
is going to happen.

184
00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:27.720
What will happen is very simple:

185
00:11:27.887 --> 00:11:30.823
You're going to do right by us.
or we will compel you to do so.

186
00:11:30.990 --> 00:11:33.755
MAN: What do you mean by "compel"?
- You know exactly what I mean.

187
00:11:33.993 --> 00:11:36.258
If you're threatening
litigation. this meeting is over.

188
00:11:36.462 --> 00:11:38.158
Then it's over.

189
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.531
MAN: Thank you for your time.

190
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:43.602
Mr. Hamlin. Mr. McGill.

191
00:11:53.379 --> 00:11:55.348
All right. Where do we start?

192
00:11:55.515 --> 00:11:57.677
Francis should start
digging into regulations.

193
00:11:57.850 --> 00:12:01.582
I'm sorry. I don't have the code
sections at my fingertips just now.

194
00:12:01.754 --> 00:12:03.450
Let's pull a team
of associates...

195
00:12:03.623 --> 00:12:07.082
and get them looking at
every angle of injunctive relief.

196
00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:09.525
Before close of business.
we'll hit Santa Rosa...

197
00:12:09.696 --> 00:12:13.189
with a demand letter
that'll make their heads spin.

198
00:12:13.366 --> 00:12:16.359
Odds are. inside a week.
they'll be sitting at the table again.

199
00:12:16.536 --> 00:12:19.096
And if not. well...

200
00:12:19.272 --> 00:12:21.798
we've never shied
away from a fight.

201
00:12:25.211 --> 00:12:26.804
Chuck. do you
remember Al McConnell?

202
00:12:27.013 --> 00:12:28.777
Of course. Hell of a litigator.

203
00:12:29.015 --> 00:12:32.452
- Retired now. isn't he?
- He's a professor at UNM now.

204
00:12:32.619 --> 00:12:35.453
Wrote a fantastic book on
SCOTUS during Reconstruction.

205
00:12:35.622 --> 00:12:36.749
Fascinating stuff.

206
00:12:36.956 --> 00:12:38.584
- Okay.
- I was talking to him...

207
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:43.624
and he mentioned he'd love
you to come speak to his One-L's.

208
00:12:43.796 --> 00:12:46.095
Maybe make it a regular
thing. if you wanted.

209
00:12:48.067 --> 00:12:50.002
What are you talking
about. Howard?

210
00:12:50.169 --> 00:12:52.001
What I'm saying is...

211
00:12:52.171 --> 00:12:55.073
maybe it's time to
hang up your spurs.

212
00:12:55.742 --> 00:12:57.176
Become partner emeritus.

213
00:12:57.343 --> 00:12:59.778
Leave your name on the
firm. but focus on your legacy.

214
00:12:59.946 --> 00:13:03.405
You always said you wanted to
work on the Commerce Clause.

215
00:13:03.583 --> 00:13:05.347
You can write the book on it.

216
00:13:05.551 --> 00:13:07.611
And no longer be
a practicing lawyer.

217
00:13:10.189 --> 00:13:11.987
Chuck. there's
more to life than this.

218
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:15.151
That day is far in
the future. Howard...

219
00:13:15.328 --> 00:13:18.560
and I don't appreciate
the suggestion.

220
00:13:19.866 --> 00:13:22.700
- What if it's not a suggestion?
- Meaning?

221
00:13:22.869 --> 00:13:25.634
Meaning if enough people
tell you that you're drunk...

222
00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:28.070
maybe it's time to sit down.

223
00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:33.203
You want me to retire over this?

224
00:13:33.379 --> 00:13:35.644
- The insurance?
- It's not just the insurance.

225
00:13:35.848 --> 00:13:38.579
That's the straw that
broke the camel's back.

226
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:42.584
Oh. so this is
about my condition.

227
00:13:42.855 --> 00:13:43.948
Look.

228
00:13:44.891 --> 00:13:46.484
Look.

229
00:13:48.494 --> 00:13:50.190
You see?

230
00:13:51.364 --> 00:13:52.957
See?

231
00:13:53.132 --> 00:13:55.101
I'm better.

232
00:13:55.368 --> 00:13:57.860
Howard. I'm fine.

233
00:14:01.207 --> 00:14:03.233
This is not what
"fine" looks like.

234
00:14:07.613 --> 00:14:09.912
Chuck. you are the best
legal mind I've ever known.

235
00:14:10.116 --> 00:14:11.982
Hands down.

236
00:14:12.385 --> 00:14:15.753
But your decision-making
has become unpredictable.

237
00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:21.051
I can't be partners with someone
whose judgment I don't trust.

238
00:14:25.565 --> 00:14:27.227
Chuck.

239
00:14:33.639 --> 00:14:35.232
[DOOR CLOSES]

240
00:14:39.545 --> 00:14:44.347
GATWOOD: This right here is
the Texas-New Mexico border.

241
00:14:44.517 --> 00:14:45.541
Now...

242
00:14:45.718 --> 00:14:48.449
all of my wells are square...

243
00:14:48.654 --> 00:14:50.748
on the Texas side.

244
00:14:50.923 --> 00:14:53.859
When I negotiated for the
mineral and property rights...

245
00:14:54.026 --> 00:14:57.394
the surveyor said that the
next nearest pool extended to...

246
00:15:02.268 --> 00:15:03.463
about here.

247
00:15:03.703 --> 00:15:05.103
Right.

248
00:15:05.271 --> 00:15:07.069
But after some extraction...

249
00:15:07.273 --> 00:15:09.799
the west wall of the
salt dome gave way...

250
00:15:09.976 --> 00:15:12.605
opening up another
pool that extends what?

251
00:15:12.779 --> 00:15:15.476
- A hundred yards over the border?
- About the size of it.

252
00:15:15.715 --> 00:15:18.947
And now you have the New
Mexico rights holders to deal with.

253
00:15:19.118 --> 00:15:20.746
They should get
profit on theirs...

254
00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:25.255
but I've got two states coming after
me for taxes on each and every gallon.

255
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:28.584
No equipment crosses the border?

256
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:30.286
No. ma'am.

257
00:15:30.463 --> 00:15:33.297
Nothing below the
surface. like the...?

258
00:15:33.833 --> 00:15:35.131
What. is it a drill bit?

259
00:15:35.334 --> 00:15:38.065
It'd be the sucker rod at this
point. but no. none of that.

260
00:15:38.237 --> 00:15:40.069
Only on the Texas side.

261
00:15:40.239 --> 00:15:43.801
That's not stopping New
Mexico from trying to bleed me.

262
00:15:43.976 --> 00:15:46.411
You said on the phone
you have a solution.

263
00:15:47.580 --> 00:15:49.776
You don't negotiate a
lease with the rights holders.

264
00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:52.282
- You offer to pay them damages.
- Damages?

265
00:15:52.452 --> 00:15:54.444
For diminishing their resource.

266
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:58.079
A significant fraction of the
value of the New Mexico portion...

267
00:15:58.257 --> 00:16:00.749
but without paying for
the rights themselves.

268
00:16:00.927 --> 00:16:03.590
So kind of a payoff.

269
00:16:04.230 --> 00:16:05.755
You don't get
hit with the taxes.

270
00:16:05.965 --> 00:16:07.934
You think you can make that fly?

271
00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:10.626
If someone came
to me with this offer...

272
00:16:10.803 --> 00:16:12.431
I'd sure as hell take it.

273
00:16:12.605 --> 00:16:15.268
Wish I'd called you sooner.

274
00:16:15.641 --> 00:16:17.041
Way they're making noise...

275
00:16:17.243 --> 00:16:19.872
if I don't get this wrapped
up by the end of the quarter...

276
00:16:20.046 --> 00:16:22.606
I'm pretty sure the tax boys
are gonna take me apart.

277
00:16:23.382 --> 00:16:25.874
And that's two weeks from now?

278
00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:29.850
I can do it by then.

279
00:16:30.022 --> 00:16:31.149
Really?

280
00:16:31.324 --> 00:16:33.054
If we get the rights
holders in one place...

281
00:16:33.259 --> 00:16:35.990
I can walk them through
what we're proposing.

282
00:16:36.162 --> 00:16:39.030
- If they're smart. they'll go for it.
- Well. hot damn.

283
00:16:42.301 --> 00:16:44.896
Kevin said you're a miracle
worker. I didn't believe him.

284
00:16:45.137 --> 00:16:46.469
I'm starting to.

285
00:16:46.639 --> 00:16:49.837
Yeah. Well. let me work that
miracle first. then we'll talk.

286
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:53.377
You know the way out of
here? I got a drill head...

287
00:16:53.546 --> 00:16:57.176
that's acting up on me out
in the north 40 I gotta check.

288
00:16:57.350 --> 00:16:58.841
Yeah. I'm good.

289
00:16:59.018 --> 00:17:01.988
You need anything from
me. you got my cell. Call me.

290
00:17:02.154 --> 00:17:03.816
Will do.

291
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:20.499
[STARTS ENGINE]

292
00:17:24.076 --> 00:17:25.738
Billy Gatwood meeting notes:

293
00:17:25.912 --> 00:17:27.073
Contact Gatwood Oil...

294
00:17:27.313 --> 00:17:30.010
get names and numbers for
New Mexico rights holders.

295
00:17:30.216 --> 00:17:31.582
[ENGINE REVVING]

296
00:17:34.420 --> 00:17:36.889
Shit.

297
00:18:37.316 --> 00:18:39.342
No. no. no!

298
00:18:39.518 --> 00:18:40.884
Shit.

299
00:18:42.188 --> 00:18:43.451
[BRAKES SQUEAK]

300
00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:52.593
[SIGHS]

301
00:19:00.940 --> 00:19:02.408
[ENGINE STARTS]

302
00:19:05.011 --> 00:19:08.379
Continuing notes from
Gatwood Oil meeting:

303
00:19:08.547 --> 00:19:10.641
Contact rights holders...

304
00:19:10.816 --> 00:19:12.216
begin scheduling.

305
00:19:25.698 --> 00:19:29.226
[JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

306
00:19:30.436 --> 00:19:31.460
[MUSIC STOPS]

307
00:19:36.242 --> 00:19:37.870
Howard.

308
00:19:40.046 --> 00:19:44.074
- What are you doing here. Jimmy?
- We have business to discuss.

309
00:19:44.250 --> 00:19:45.650
Is this about Chuck?

310
00:19:46.218 --> 00:19:47.447
Who?

311
00:19:48.087 --> 00:19:50.181
If you have business.
then call my secretary.

312
00:19:50.356 --> 00:19:53.019
I did. She stonewalled
me. as if you didn't know.

313
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:54.192
Sandpiper.

314
00:19:54.727 --> 00:19:56.423
- What about it?
- It's time to settle.

315
00:19:56.595 --> 00:19:58.086
I saw the current offer.

316
00:19:58.264 --> 00:20:02.258
The clients make their losses
back. plus a solid chunk of change.

317
00:20:02.535 --> 00:20:04.367
Not that it's any
of your business...

318
00:20:04.537 --> 00:20:07.063
but we project a number
higher than the current offer.

319
00:20:07.239 --> 00:20:08.764
I get it. I get it.
You hold out...

320
00:20:08.974 --> 00:20:11.205
maybe you squeeze a
grand more for each client.

321
00:20:11.377 --> 00:20:14.006
Meanwhile. HHM nets
a few million. you know?

322
00:20:14.180 --> 00:20:16.445
You're screwing the
clients for your own benefit.

323
00:20:16.615 --> 00:20:19.278
Oh. so now you're
worried about the clients?

324
00:20:19.485 --> 00:20:21.420
It's the right thing to
do. and you know it.

325
00:20:21.587 --> 00:20:22.611
Please.

326
00:20:22.788 --> 00:20:25.417
All you care about is
your share of the payout.

327
00:20:25.591 --> 00:20:26.615
[CHUCKLES]

328
00:20:26.792 --> 00:20:28.693
It's like talking to Gollum.

329
00:20:28.861 --> 00:20:32.195
You're transparent and pathetic.

330
00:20:33.132 --> 00:20:34.998
You want a handout?

331
00:20:36.435 --> 00:20:37.869
Here.

332
00:20:39.705 --> 00:20:40.705
Huh?

333
00:20:42.208 --> 00:20:43.904
Next time...

334
00:20:44.076 --> 00:20:45.601
why don't you bring a tin cup?

335
00:20:45.778 --> 00:20:47.770
It'd be more honest.

336
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:50.614
Listen. Howard.

337
00:20:50.783 --> 00:20:53.378
Settle this now. It's in
everyone's best interests.

338
00:20:53.552 --> 00:20:55.646
Meaning it's in
your best interests.

339
00:20:55.821 --> 00:20:57.585
And if we don't. what
are you gonna do?

340
00:20:57.757 --> 00:21:00.659
Peel off members of the class.
leak insider info to Schweikart?

341
00:21:01.260 --> 00:21:02.284
Oh. I doubt it.

342
00:21:02.461 --> 00:21:05.329
I know you're low enough to do
that. but you're too damn greedy.

343
00:21:05.531 --> 00:21:08.626
You do any of that. you'll
be jeopardizing your payday.

344
00:21:10.102 --> 00:21:12.003
You'll get your damn money...

345
00:21:12.171 --> 00:21:14.106
you're just gonna
have to wait for it.

346
00:21:15.641 --> 00:21:17.633
[LIGHTER CLICKING]

347
00:21:49.175 --> 00:21:50.871
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

348
00:22:00.519 --> 00:22:02.681
[IN SPANISH]
What's so important?

349
00:22:02.888 --> 00:22:04.833
BOLSA [IN SPANISH OVER
PHONE]: <i>Had a conversation...</i>

350
00:22:04.857 --> 00:22:06.348
<i>with our friend by the pool.</i>

351
00:22:06.525 --> 00:22:09.222
<i>He's very pleased
with our progress.</i>

352
00:22:09.395 --> 00:22:13.093
<i>He feels our consolidated
transportation method is working.</i>

353
00:22:14.200 --> 00:22:16.396
<i>In fact. it works so well...</i>

354
00:22:16.602 --> 00:22:21.700
<i>that our friend says this will be
the only way. moving forward.</i>

355
00:22:22.842 --> 00:22:25.971
<i>Of course. your territory
will stay yours forever.</i>

356
00:22:26.145 --> 00:22:30.014
<i>But this system has
less exposure. Less risk.</i>

357
00:22:30.549 --> 00:22:33.144
<i>Everything moves
through the Chilean.</i>

358
00:22:41.427 --> 00:22:42.895
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

359
00:22:49.835 --> 00:22:51.895
I hear you.

360
00:22:53.005 --> 00:22:54.098
[IN SPANISH] Don Hector...

361
00:22:54.273 --> 00:22:56.833
I never asked for
this. I do not want it.

362
00:23:06.652 --> 00:23:07.779
NACHO: Don Hector.

363
00:23:08.020 --> 00:23:09.283
[HECTOR GRUNTING]

364
00:23:09.455 --> 00:23:11.447
[♪♪♪]

365
00:23:16.662 --> 00:23:18.290
[GASPING]

366
00:23:41.954 --> 00:23:45.550
Fuck Eladio...

367
00:23:45.724 --> 00:23:47.989
fuck Bolsa...

368
00:23:48.193 --> 00:23:50.253
and fuck you.

369
00:24:03.709 --> 00:24:05.905
[LIGHT POP MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

370
00:24:13.218 --> 00:24:15.210
[MAN SINGING INDISTINCTLY
OVER SPEAKERS]

371
00:24:35.874 --> 00:24:38.036
[WOMEN CHATTERING NEARBY]

372
00:24:41.780 --> 00:24:45.842
WOMAN: Well. we go around
about. you know. six times. I think.

373
00:24:46.018 --> 00:24:47.646
I think we're... Yeah.

374
00:24:47.820 --> 00:24:49.618
I think... I think so.

375
00:24:51.690 --> 00:24:54.489
I know. It's just
so good for you.

376
00:24:54.660 --> 00:24:56.026
JIMMY: Hello. ladies.

377
00:24:56.261 --> 00:24:57.456
Good morning.

378
00:24:57.629 --> 00:24:59.063
- Jimmy?
- Hi. Jimmy.

379
00:24:59.264 --> 00:25:04.703
Jimmy. You girls go on a
little bit. I'll catch up with you.

380
00:25:04.903 --> 00:25:05.903
[LAUGHS]

381
00:25:06.071 --> 00:25:09.530
Wow. Irene. Fancy running
into you twice in one week.

382
00:25:09.708 --> 00:25:10.835
How lucky am I?

383
00:25:11.043 --> 00:25:13.638
You're a mall-walker?
I had no idea.

384
00:25:13.812 --> 00:25:16.077
Me? Oh. yeah. big-time.

385
00:25:16.281 --> 00:25:22.221
I mean. it's great for cardio.
hamstrings. glutes. IT band.

386
00:25:22.388 --> 00:25:25.358
I'm a huge mall-walker. Been
out of the game for a while.

387
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:28.983
Developed this damn plantar
fasciitis. Hurts like a bear.

388
00:25:29.194 --> 00:25:31.595
Oh. I'm so sorry
to hear about that.

389
00:25:32.097 --> 00:25:35.727
Well. hey. I got
the cure right here.

390
00:25:36.568 --> 00:25:37.661
Pow!

391
00:25:37.836 --> 00:25:41.295
These have a special
gel and resistance coils...

392
00:25:41.507 --> 00:25:44.568
and a bunch of stuff. It's
like walking on pillows.

393
00:25:44.743 --> 00:25:47.770
Well. they look comfortable.

394
00:25:47.946 --> 00:25:49.039
You like them?

395
00:25:49.415 --> 00:25:52.317
Well. they...
They're quite stylish.

396
00:25:52.818 --> 00:25:54.514
Hey. you know what?

397
00:25:54.753 --> 00:25:58.520
I bought a pair for my girlfriend. and
they don't fit. and the store has this...

398
00:25:58.690 --> 00:26:01.216
Wouldn't you know it?
- -no-refunds policy.

399
00:26:01.427 --> 00:26:02.827
What size are you?

400
00:26:03.862 --> 00:26:07.128
Seven and a half.
seven and a half.

401
00:26:07.933 --> 00:26:10.869
Seven and a half.
Oh. there you go.

402
00:26:18.410 --> 00:26:20.276
- How does that feel?
- Oh...

403
00:26:22.714 --> 00:26:24.546
I... I see what you mean.

404
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:29.381
They are so nice. and
they fit like a dream.

405
00:26:29.555 --> 00:26:31.956
But I can't take
these for free. Jimmy.

406
00:26:32.157 --> 00:26:33.887
Oh. please.

407
00:26:34.059 --> 00:26:37.996
- There is one thing you could do for me.
- What's that?

408
00:26:38.163 --> 00:26:40.155
Don't tell the other
folks I gave them to you.

409
00:26:40.365 --> 00:26:42.664
I don't wanna look like
I'm playing favorites.

410
00:26:42.868 --> 00:26:44.166
My lips are sealed.

411
00:26:44.369 --> 00:26:47.100
Then you enjoy those. I'm gonna
go get my heart rate back up.

412
00:26:47.272 --> 00:26:48.570
- Oh. thank you.
- See you later.

413
00:26:48.740 --> 00:26:51.141
Thank you so much. Jimmy.

414
00:26:52.478 --> 00:26:53.502
[EXHALES]

415
00:26:53.679 --> 00:26:54.874
[♪♪♪]

416
00:27:00.119 --> 00:27:03.647
<i>the hand of love. Now. watch.
and I'll show you the story of life...</i>

417
00:27:03.889 --> 00:27:06.518
JIMMY: You've got some
questions. It's only natural.

418
00:27:06.692 --> 00:27:11.187
And the truth is. if Irene
settles. you'd get some money.

419
00:27:12.631 --> 00:27:15.465
But. I mean. it's not like
you guys need it. right?

420
00:27:16.668 --> 00:27:19.137
On the other hand. I did
get a look at their offer...

421
00:27:19.304 --> 00:27:22.638
and I don't wanna speak
out of school. but it's. uh:

422
00:27:22.808 --> 00:27:23.935
[WHISTLES]

423
00:27:24.710 --> 00:27:29.011
But. I mean. hey. everyone's
situation is different.

424
00:27:29.348 --> 00:27:31.783
Maybe Irene just
doesn't need the money.

425
00:27:31.984 --> 00:27:33.543
I don't know for a fact. but...

426
00:27:33.986 --> 00:27:36.820
when you see someone
buying nice new things...

427
00:27:36.989 --> 00:27:38.787
- Like those shoes.
- Like those shoes.

428
00:27:38.991 --> 00:27:40.152
Uh-huh.

429
00:27:41.193 --> 00:27:43.059
JIMMY: <i>Those must
have cost a pretty penny.</i>

430
00:27:43.295 --> 00:27:46.424
<i>If she can afford those.
she's walking on easy street.</i>

431
00:27:46.632 --> 00:27:49.363
And there's something else.

432
00:27:49.668 --> 00:27:51.068
You know. the lawyers?

433
00:27:51.303 --> 00:27:55.502
I mean. that's the lawyers'
share of the settlement...

434
00:27:55.674 --> 00:27:59.236
and your share
is this much. Doot.

435
00:27:59.444 --> 00:28:01.379
If Irene holds out...

436
00:28:01.547 --> 00:28:04.039
the lawyers get
this much more...

437
00:28:04.249 --> 00:28:06.809
and you are gonna
get this much more.

438
00:28:08.353 --> 00:28:10.185
Doesn't seem like
much difference.

439
00:28:10.389 --> 00:28:12.756
JIMMY: I know. but
that's how it works.

440
00:28:12.991 --> 00:28:16.257
And Irene knows it too. I mean.
the lawyers have explained it to her.

441
00:28:17.095 --> 00:28:19.360
<i>It's crazy. but
it's all up to Irene.</i>

442
00:28:19.531 --> 00:28:22.228
<i>After all. she is the
class representative.</i>

443
00:28:22.401 --> 00:28:25.030
Does that mean
that she gets more?

444
00:28:25.204 --> 00:28:29.699
No. no. It just means in the
eyes of the court. she's special.

445
00:28:29.875 --> 00:28:32.902
She's like your
congressman or ambassador.

446
00:28:33.111 --> 00:28:34.875
ROSE: Is there
anything we can do?

447
00:28:35.047 --> 00:28:36.413
No.

448
00:28:36.582 --> 00:28:38.881
No. You can't do anything.

449
00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:41.213
I can't do anything.

450
00:28:41.587 --> 00:28:44.386
Only Irene.

451
00:28:45.891 --> 00:28:47.689
She probably knows what's best.

452
00:28:47.893 --> 00:28:50.863
I'm sure she's taking
your feelings into account.

453
00:28:51.063 --> 00:28:53.294
Hey. look at the big picture.

454
00:28:53.532 --> 00:28:56.127
Who needs money when
you got the moral high ground?

455
00:28:57.803 --> 00:28:59.635
[JIMMY EXHALING]

456
00:29:02.140 --> 00:29:03.438
Yoo-hoo!

457
00:29:03.909 --> 00:29:05.775
Rose.

458
00:29:06.144 --> 00:29:07.772
Helen.

459
00:29:08.747 --> 00:29:10.375
Ladies?

460
00:29:10.716 --> 00:29:12.912
Ladies?

461
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:47.450
[WOMAN SPEAKING
IN SPANISH OVER TV]

462
00:29:48.553 --> 00:29:50.044
[TV CLICKS OFF]

463
00:29:54.993 --> 00:29:56.359
[IN SPANISH] Ignacio?

464
00:29:56.828 --> 00:29:58.353
[IN SPANISH] Hey. Dad.

465
00:29:59.498 --> 00:30:01.694
I was falling
asleep to the news.

466
00:30:02.668 --> 00:30:04.068
NACHO: Yeah. I know.

467
00:30:05.871 --> 00:30:07.271
Are you all right. <i>mijo?</i>

468
00:30:17.683 --> 00:30:18.683
Dad...

469
00:30:21.320 --> 00:30:23.789
A man is going to
come to your shop. Soon.

470
00:30:24.456 --> 00:30:25.480
A bad man.

471
00:30:26.958 --> 00:30:27.958
What?

472
00:30:28.393 --> 00:30:31.227
He'll want to run
the place for a while.

473
00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:34.827
And you'll have to let him.

474
00:30:39.371 --> 00:30:40.896
Do you understand?

475
00:30:41.139 --> 00:30:43.199
And who is this man?

476
00:30:48.213 --> 00:30:49.841
Hector Salamanca.

477
00:30:53.652 --> 00:30:55.484
Salamanca.

478
00:30:57.222 --> 00:31:00.056
I've been working
for them again.

479
00:31:02.861 --> 00:31:03.920
[SIGHS]

480
00:31:04.129 --> 00:31:06.724
I know what you're thinking.

481
00:31:06.898 --> 00:31:08.423
And you can scream at me...

482
00:31:08.633 --> 00:31:09.692
disown me...

483
00:31:09.868 --> 00:31:13.168
never speak to me again.
but whatever happens...

484
00:31:13.572 --> 00:31:15.268
you must do what he says.

485
00:31:17.142 --> 00:31:20.340
I know what you're
gonna want to do.

486
00:31:22.247 --> 00:31:23.909
But you can't.

487
00:31:25.717 --> 00:31:27.379
You can't. Dad.

488
00:31:27.652 --> 00:31:31.953
Do what he says. this will
blow over in a few weeks.

489
00:31:33.291 --> 00:31:35.419
If you don't...

490
00:31:37.362 --> 00:31:39.058
I swear.

491
00:31:39.431 --> 00:31:42.560
I swear it'll be over soon.

492
00:31:46.371 --> 00:31:48.966
How can I believe
anything you say?

493
00:31:50.475 --> 00:31:54.037
Promise me you won't
do anything stupid.

494
00:32:00.051 --> 00:32:02.611
Promise me. Dad.

495
00:32:04.623 --> 00:32:06.387
Please.

496
00:32:11.196 --> 00:32:13.461
Get out of my house.

497
00:32:47.432 --> 00:32:48.991
[DOOR CLOSES]

498
00:32:57.542 --> 00:32:59.977
FRANCIS: I'm still waiting for
those third-party subpoenas.

499
00:33:00.145 --> 00:33:02.774
- Great. Let me know. Thanks. Francis.
- All right.

500
00:33:02.981 --> 00:33:04.779
Julie. what's up?

501
00:33:04.950 --> 00:33:06.714
From Chuck. It
came via messenger.

502
00:33:06.885 --> 00:33:10.378
The instructions say he wants
you to read it as soon as possible.

503
00:33:12.023 --> 00:33:13.355
[CHUCKLES]

504
00:33:14.059 --> 00:33:16.358
Uh. here's what I need
you to do: call around.

505
00:33:16.528 --> 00:33:19.362
Find someplace special
for the retirement party.

506
00:33:19.531 --> 00:33:22.968
Something classy. old
school. La Posada. maybe.

507
00:33:23.134 --> 00:33:25.626
And a band. something
jazzy. Upbeat.

508
00:33:26.271 --> 00:33:28.035
Find what's available.
Let's set it up.

509
00:33:28.206 --> 00:33:29.640
Okay.

510
00:33:43.021 --> 00:33:44.512
Goddamn it. Chuck.

511
00:33:47.225 --> 00:33:49.057
You're suing Hamlin
Hamlin McGill?

512
00:33:49.427 --> 00:33:51.225
Come on in. Howard.

513
00:33:54.599 --> 00:33:56.158
You turned the lights on?

514
00:33:56.334 --> 00:33:57.893
I told you.

515
00:33:58.069 --> 00:33:59.697
I'm back to normal.

516
00:34:00.071 --> 00:34:03.200
And. yes. I am suing
HHM for breach of contract.

517
00:34:03.375 --> 00:34:05.503
Do you have any
idea what you're doing?

518
00:34:05.677 --> 00:34:08.875
I believe I do. I'm
calling your bluff.

519
00:34:09.047 --> 00:34:11.744
This is my firm. I built it.

520
00:34:11.917 --> 00:34:15.183
Your father was working in a
two-room office when I joined him.

521
00:34:15.387 --> 00:34:18.186
And you. I tutored
for the bar exam.

522
00:34:18.356 --> 00:34:19.585
You're not kicking me out.

523
00:34:19.891 --> 00:34:23.384
If you can't "trust my
judgment." as you say. so be it...

524
00:34:23.562 --> 00:34:26.054
but you're gonna have
to pay me for my share.

525
00:34:26.264 --> 00:34:29.359
I believe that comes
to around $8 million.

526
00:34:29.534 --> 00:34:32.231
We both know the firm
doesn't have the money.

527
00:34:33.705 --> 00:34:35.936
You'd rather tear
down HHM than retire?

528
00:34:36.141 --> 00:34:39.111
You think I'm trouble
now as your partner?

529
00:34:39.277 --> 00:34:40.711
Imagine me as your enemy.

530
00:34:44.349 --> 00:34:45.578
[WHIRRING]

531
00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:47.150
Chuck.

532
00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:49.486
The damage you're going to do...

533
00:34:49.654 --> 00:34:53.113
If you'd like to discuss
this further. we can. in court.

534
00:34:53.892 --> 00:34:55.724
Until then...

535
00:34:56.294 --> 00:34:58.456
what else is there to say?

536
00:34:59.664 --> 00:35:01.098
[WHIRRING RESUMES]

537
00:35:14.646 --> 00:35:17.138
[GROANS]

538
00:35:17.315 --> 00:35:19.147
Blue pot. Red wine.

539
00:35:19.317 --> 00:35:20.808
Black burner.

540
00:35:20.986 --> 00:35:23.148
Blue pot. Red wine.

541
00:35:23.888 --> 00:35:27.120
Black burner. Black
burner. Black burner.

542
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:29.693
