543
00:35:30.195 --> 00:35:32.494
[EXHALING SHARPLY]

544
00:36:16.875 --> 00:36:19.367
JIMMY: I got hot
hands. I got hot hands.

545
00:36:19.544 --> 00:36:23.311
I know this is gonna
be the one. B-9.

546
00:36:23.515 --> 00:36:28.044
Let's hope that biopsy
comes back "B-9."

547
00:36:28.219 --> 00:36:30.347
B-9.

548
00:36:33.058 --> 00:36:36.256
Okay. What's next?

549
00:36:36.461 --> 00:36:38.692
We got I-29.

550
00:36:38.863 --> 00:36:41.230
I remember when I was 29.

551
00:36:41.466 --> 00:36:43.264
I bet you do too.

552
00:36:43.735 --> 00:36:45.897
I-29.

553
00:36:51.609 --> 00:36:54.477
Here comes O-62.

554
00:36:56.181 --> 00:37:00.778
Oh. my God. Have I called 62
of these already? Feels like it.

555
00:37:00.985 --> 00:37:03.386
O-62.

556
00:37:04.189 --> 00:37:07.751
Here we have B-2. B-2.

557
00:37:07.992 --> 00:37:10.393
Well. tonight it is all bingo.

558
00:37:10.562 --> 00:37:11.757
Here it comes.

559
00:37:11.996 --> 00:37:14.261
O-70. anyone? O-70.

560
00:37:15.200 --> 00:37:17.260
All right. No takers.

561
00:37:17.502 --> 00:37:19.095
Boom.

562
00:37:19.437 --> 00:37:22.202
G-55. G-55.

563
00:37:22.373 --> 00:37:25.775
Oh. my God. bingo. I got bingo.

564
00:37:26.010 --> 00:37:28.878
Big Paul. bring it up.
Kelley. take a look.

565
00:37:29.047 --> 00:37:30.047
[CLAPPING AND CHEERING]

566
00:37:30.215 --> 00:37:32.081
We may have a winner.

567
00:37:33.084 --> 00:37:34.211
Kelley. tell me.

568
00:37:34.385 --> 00:37:37.549
Have we got it? We
have a bingo: Paul.

569
00:37:37.722 --> 00:37:40.419
Step up to the winner's
circle. Let's hear it for him.

570
00:37:40.625 --> 00:37:42.617
Let's give him a big
round of applause.

571
00:37:45.396 --> 00:37:47.297
Okay. New game. new cards.

572
00:37:47.465 --> 00:37:48.489
Here they come.

573
00:37:48.666 --> 00:37:52.330
Get yourself some
new cards. new cards.

574
00:37:52.837 --> 00:37:53.964
The helpers have them.

575
00:37:54.172 --> 00:37:57.904
You can have one. two. You
can have up to four. as you know.

576
00:37:58.176 --> 00:38:00.771
Here's a lucky blue one for you.

577
00:38:00.945 --> 00:38:04.279
All right. Take your cards
so we can start a new game.

578
00:38:04.449 --> 00:38:07.317
There you go. Add
that to your stack.

579
00:38:08.586 --> 00:38:10.145
All right. Get your cards.

580
00:38:10.321 --> 00:38:12.290
Hey. Irene. You
feeling lucky today?

581
00:38:12.757 --> 00:38:14.157
I guess so.

582
00:38:14.359 --> 00:38:16.919
All right. Well.
here's one on me.

583
00:38:17.295 --> 00:38:18.354
Just for you.

584
00:38:19.297 --> 00:38:20.297
All right.

585
00:38:20.465 --> 00:38:24.630
I sold my soul
for B-I-N-G and O.

586
00:38:24.936 --> 00:38:26.802
Let's clear the table.

587
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:48.687
Load it up.

588
00:38:48.893 --> 00:38:50.885
[♪♪♪]

589
00:38:55.099 --> 00:38:56.533
Locked and loaded.

590
00:39:03.842 --> 00:39:05.970
Here comes a new game.

591
00:39:11.049 --> 00:39:12.881
First number up.

592
00:39:15.153 --> 00:39:17.520
It's N-31.

593
00:39:18.022 --> 00:39:19.022
N for "Nancy."

594
00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:22.319
Thirty-one for the number of
times she told me to take a hike.

595
00:39:22.560 --> 00:39:25.257
N-31.

596
00:39:27.665 --> 00:39:32.035
G-48. G for the
"Greatest Generation."

597
00:39:32.237 --> 00:39:34.832
Forty-eight for "Dewey
defeats Truman."

598
00:39:35.373 --> 00:39:37.933
Here's I-25. The big I.

599
00:39:38.409 --> 00:39:41.436
I-25. It's B-12.

600
00:39:42.013 --> 00:39:43.845
Like the vitamin.

601
00:39:51.856 --> 00:39:53.449
O-67.

602
00:39:53.691 --> 00:39:56.889
Anybody? I got a
good feeling about this.

603
00:39:57.095 --> 00:39:59.360
O-67.

604
00:40:01.232 --> 00:40:03.667
I... I think bingo!

605
00:40:04.702 --> 00:40:05.863
Who is that?

606
00:40:06.037 --> 00:40:07.767
Come on up.

607
00:40:08.172 --> 00:40:11.574
Irene? Irene. come
on up here. dear.

608
00:40:12.377 --> 00:40:14.278
Bring it up to Kelley.
Let's take a look.

609
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:17.875
Kelley has to check your card.

610
00:40:19.183 --> 00:40:21.584
Here she comes.

611
00:40:25.823 --> 00:40:27.951
Could be.

612
00:40:30.428 --> 00:40:32.454
Oh. my goodness.

613
00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:36.465
It is a bingo for Irene.

614
00:40:36.701 --> 00:40:38.693
Let's hear it for Irene Landry.

615
00:40:38.903 --> 00:40:40.599
[FAINT APPLAUSE]

616
00:40:40.772 --> 00:40:44.231
Give it up for the big
winner. Irene Landry.

617
00:40:45.443 --> 00:40:47.275
Fastest bingo of the night.

618
00:40:47.812 --> 00:40:50.145
Come on. Let's
hear it for Irene.

619
00:40:50.348 --> 00:40:51.646
[GROANS]

620
00:40:51.816 --> 00:40:53.148
[SOBBING]

621
00:40:53.318 --> 00:40:54.342
Irene?

622
00:40:54.519 --> 00:40:55.851
Where are you going...? Hey...

623
00:40:56.020 --> 00:40:57.955
You know what? Take over.

624
00:40:59.290 --> 00:41:00.290
Okay.

625
00:41:00.458 --> 00:41:01.458
Time for a new game.

626
00:41:01.626 --> 00:41:03.925
Uh. let's get some
cards out for everyone.

627
00:41:04.729 --> 00:41:06.823
[IRENE SOBBING]

628
00:41:10.268 --> 00:41:13.363
Hey. what's going on? You okay?

629
00:41:15.273 --> 00:41:17.208
Oh. don't do that.

630
00:41:17.375 --> 00:41:20.368
Your mascara's
gonna run all over.

631
00:41:22.780 --> 00:41:24.544
Irene. come on.

632
00:41:24.749 --> 00:41:26.377
What's wrong?

633
00:41:28.186 --> 00:41:31.623
They've all turned on me.

634
00:41:32.123 --> 00:41:34.024
Who has?

635
00:41:34.359 --> 00:41:35.987
My friends.

636
00:41:36.160 --> 00:41:39.221
Helen. Rose. Myrtle.

637
00:41:39.397 --> 00:41:40.524
All of them.

638
00:41:41.366 --> 00:41:44.359
What? No.

639
00:41:44.535 --> 00:41:46.265
Yes.

640
00:41:47.372 --> 00:41:50.206
They're so cold.

641
00:41:50.908 --> 00:41:54.470
When I walk past them.
they stop talking. and...

642
00:41:54.645 --> 00:41:59.083
I hear them whispering
when they think I'm not there.

643
00:41:59.283 --> 00:42:01.514
It's just so...

644
00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:05.782
They're so cruel. and
I don't even know why.

645
00:42:10.928 --> 00:42:12.726
I think. uh...

646
00:42:13.331 --> 00:42:15.163
maybe I do.

647
00:42:16.934 --> 00:42:18.562
You do?

648
00:42:22.440 --> 00:42:25.035
Could it be the settlement?

649
00:42:25.209 --> 00:42:30.011
I mean. maybe they
want the money...

650
00:42:30.181 --> 00:42:33.549
you know. to
improve their lives?

651
00:42:33.718 --> 00:42:36.620
I had no idea any of
them needed money.

652
00:42:36.854 --> 00:42:38.914
No one said anything to me.

653
00:42:39.090 --> 00:42:41.355
Well. maybe it's not
about the money itself.

654
00:42:41.559 --> 00:42:43.027
I mean. although...

655
00:42:43.194 --> 00:42:45.754
who wouldn't want more money?

656
00:42:46.197 --> 00:42:49.258
I mean. maybe
it's the idea that...

657
00:42:49.600 --> 00:42:54.129
they don't think you're
considering them. you know?

658
00:42:54.338 --> 00:42:56.364
Thinking of their needs.

659
00:42:56.707 --> 00:42:58.733
I... I didn't know.

660
00:42:59.110 --> 00:43:02.945
I don't wanna hurt
them. They're my friends.

661
00:43:05.149 --> 00:43:07.550
I wish we'd never
even started this lawsuit.

662
00:43:07.718 --> 00:43:10.278
I just want everything
to go back the way it was.

663
00:43:13.624 --> 00:43:16.093
What should I do?

664
00:43:17.161 --> 00:43:18.891
What would you do?

665
00:43:21.766 --> 00:43:25.362
I mean. you know I'm
not a lawyer right now.

666
00:43:26.504 --> 00:43:28.063
Please?

667
00:43:29.307 --> 00:43:31.299
Should I settle?

668
00:43:35.780 --> 00:43:37.408
Irene...

669
00:43:39.317 --> 00:43:40.649
[SIGHS]

670
00:43:40.818 --> 00:43:42.252
you listen to your heart.

671
00:43:55.533 --> 00:43:58.025
- Uh. time?
- Two hours out.

672
00:43:58.202 --> 00:43:59.670
When did I say I
was gonna leave?

673
00:43:59.837 --> 00:44:01.396
Twenty minutes ago.

674
00:44:02.340 --> 00:44:04.707
Uh. can I have some
more coffee. please?

675
00:44:04.909 --> 00:44:06.138
Coming.

676
00:44:11.782 --> 00:44:14.308
Uh. I'm missing a
survey history in this one.

677
00:44:14.986 --> 00:44:16.420
On it. Sorry about that.

678
00:44:17.788 --> 00:44:19.120
Not a problem.

679
00:44:19.724 --> 00:44:23.126
Hey. who's ready to
have her life changed?

680
00:44:23.294 --> 00:44:24.294
Kim. did you hear me?

681
00:44:24.495 --> 00:44:26.191
Yep. I heard you. Life changed.

682
00:44:26.430 --> 00:44:30.367
Heh. Stop your work.
both of you. for a sec.

683
00:44:30.535 --> 00:44:31.833
I got big. big news.

684
00:44:32.036 --> 00:44:34.904
Can you just tell us later?
I'm so late. it's not even funny.

685
00:44:35.072 --> 00:44:38.201
Mesa Verde can
wait. Look. I got Zafiro.

686
00:44:38.376 --> 00:44:41.642
It's not Mesa Verde. It's a new
client. and if I mess up. a former client.

687
00:44:41.846 --> 00:44:43.747
I thought Mesa Verde
was your one and only.

688
00:44:43.948 --> 00:44:45.644
No. it's... I'm sorry.

689
00:44:45.850 --> 00:44:47.580
Can I explain this
to you later? I'm...

690
00:44:47.752 --> 00:44:49.983
Sandpiper is settling.

691
00:44:50.721 --> 00:44:52.485
- What?
- Yeah.

692
00:44:52.990 --> 00:44:54.891
For a bundle.

693
00:44:55.693 --> 00:44:59.027
But they can't be settling.
Class actions don't move that fast.

694
00:44:59.197 --> 00:45:01.325
Don't get bogged
down in the details.

695
00:45:01.499 --> 00:45:03.400
Trust me. They're settling.

696
00:45:06.070 --> 00:45:08.767
- Wow. that... That's great. then.
- Yeah. Yeah.

697
00:45:08.973 --> 00:45:10.566
So. hey. let's celebrate.

698
00:45:10.741 --> 00:45:14.701
I can tell that you pulled another
all-nighter here. you know?

699
00:45:14.879 --> 00:45:16.939
You gotta stop
and smell the roses.

700
00:45:17.114 --> 00:45:20.209
Hey. who's got two
thumbs. a bottle of Zafiro...

701
00:45:20.384 --> 00:45:22.080
and 20 percent of
the common fund?

702
00:45:22.253 --> 00:45:25.746
- This guy.
- I know. You do. Uh. I am happy for you.

703
00:45:25.923 --> 00:45:26.923
Be happy for us.

704
00:45:27.124 --> 00:45:29.093
This is the solution
to everything.

705
00:45:29.260 --> 00:45:31.559
- Okay. Could you put these all in my car?
- Kim.

706
00:45:32.363 --> 00:45:34.923
- Yeah. Jimmy. I gotta go.
- Give me five goddamn minutes.

707
00:45:35.733 --> 00:45:37.711
- I don't have five minutes.
- You're already late.

708
00:45:37.735 --> 00:45:39.931
What's five more minutes?
Drive 60 instead of 55.

709
00:45:40.104 --> 00:45:41.732
- Jimmy.
- What...?

710
00:45:41.939 --> 00:45:45.034
You're not hearing me. Our
troubles are over. Come on.

711
00:45:45.209 --> 00:45:47.872
Jimmy. I'm leaving now.
I'll be back in a few hours.

712
00:45:48.045 --> 00:45:50.879
Think of all the things you wanna
say to me and say them later.

713
00:45:51.048 --> 00:45:52.107
Goodbye.

714
00:45:52.283 --> 00:45:53.876
[DOOR CLOSES]

715
00:45:58.889 --> 00:46:00.721
[DOOR OPENS]

716
00:46:04.061 --> 00:46:06.030
You. Shots.

717
00:46:06.230 --> 00:46:08.222
- Uh. I...
- Shots.

718
00:46:08.399 --> 00:46:09.833
We're celebrating.

719
00:46:16.240 --> 00:46:17.833
Cheers.

720
00:46:21.979 --> 00:46:22.979
Smooth.

721
00:46:24.649 --> 00:46:26.174
[TAPPING FINGERS ON TABLE]

722
00:46:26.350 --> 00:46:27.784
Yeah.

723
00:46:32.189 --> 00:46:35.990
Under the terms we're offering.
you get a substantial payment...

724
00:46:36.193 --> 00:46:39.322
without any impact to your
property via drilling and extraction...

725
00:46:39.497 --> 00:46:43.832
and rather than waiting years to close.
Mr. Gatwood is offering cash. right now.

726
00:46:44.602 --> 00:46:46.662
Given the cost of overhead...

727
00:46:46.837 --> 00:46:49.705
liabilities and other burdens
Mr. Gatwood assumes...

728
00:46:49.874 --> 00:46:52.366
we believe this offer
is more than fair.

729
00:46:52.576 --> 00:46:54.204
We believe...

730
00:46:54.679 --> 00:46:57.843
We believe this
offer is more than fair.

731
00:47:11.862 --> 00:47:13.296
[GASPS]

732
00:47:17.134 --> 00:47:19.296
[PANTING]

733
00:47:37.188 --> 00:47:38.747
[GROANING]

